20their%20ability%20to%20spot%20scams%2C%20but%20scammers%20are%20evolving%20just%20as%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryn%20Thompson%2C%20the%20marketing%20director%20of%20Phonely%2C%20a%20scam-protection%20telephone%20service%20provider%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20romance%20scams%20in%20particular%2C%20scammers%20exploit%20emotional%20connections%20and%20rapidly%20build%20trust%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20financial%20exploitation%20before%20the%20victim%20even%20realizes%20what's%20happening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20long%20been%20a%20clich%C3%A9%20that%20those%20who%20get%20wrapped%20up%20in%20romance%20scams%20are%20older%20because%20they%20have%20a%20smaller%20social%20circle%2C%20are%20divorced%20or%20separated%2C%20and%20are%20simply%20more%20lonely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20went%20to%20college%20or%20started%20their%20careers%20during%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%2C%20meaning%20several%20of%20their%20formative%20years%20were%20interrupted%2C%20leaving%20them%20longing%20for%20connections%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatfishing%20is%20rife%20on%20dating%20apps%2C%20as%20are%20the%20filters%20and%20subtle%20image%20and%20video%20enhancers%20that%20have%20become%20so%20ingrained%20in%20social%20media%20posts%20that%20they%20are%20almost%20undetectable.%20All%20of%20which%20forms%20a%20gray%20area%20where%20scammers%20can%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ddd9e651-9ca9-400e-928f-a154f7fee890%5C%22%3ETrust%20in%20the%20internet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Better%20Business%20Bureau%20survey%20of%201%2C027%20respondents%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20released%20in%20April%2C%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loses-more-money-to-online-scams-than-boomers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%20lose%20more%20money%20to%20internet%20scams%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20baby%20boomers%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Annual%20Cybersecurity%20Attitudes%20and%20Behaviors%20Report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F20740408.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net%2Fhubfs%2F20740408%2FCYBSAFE-Oh%2520behave%2520report%25202022-220927%2520MS%2520-%2520V1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20by%20the%20National%20Cybersecurity%20Alliance%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20surveyed%20over%203%2C000%20people%20from%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20and%20Canada%20and%20found%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20noted%20a%20higher%20rate%20of%20falling%20for%20romance%20scams%20(15%25)%20than%20Gen%20Xers%20(8%25)%20and%20baby%20boomers%20(4%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScams%20are%20always%20evolving%2C%20and%20the%20tricks%20Gen%20Zers%20believe%20they%20are%20wise%20to%20may%20be%20replaced%20by%20increasingly%20technologically%20advanced%20schemes%20they%20don't%20see%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Hendry%20Parsons%2C%20the%20head%20of%20communications%20at%20ExpressVPN%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20more%20acquainted%20with%20meeting%20people%20online%20and%20having%20entire%20relationships%20through%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20willingness%20to%20talk%20to%20someone%20you%20don't%20know%20online%20goes%20exponentially%20up%20depending%20on%20how%20young%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Hendry%20Parsons%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhich%20opens%20that%20extra%20channel%20for%20potential%20exposure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be523e56-6dc4-4327-9abd-28a955ee181c%5C%22%3EOverconfident%20about%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kevin%20Lee%2C%20the%20trust%20and%20safety%20architect%20at%20the%20fraud%20prevention%20platform%20Sift%2C%20the%20assumption%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20too%20savvy%20to%20fall%20for%20a%20romance%20scam%20may%20leave%20them%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsift.com%2Findex-reports-ai-fraud-q2-2024%3FaliId%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20Sift%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201%2C066%20US%20adults%20earlier%20this%20year%20found%20that%2081%2