0probabilities%20suggest%20a%20near-zero%20chance%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20hold%20rates%20steady.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20time%20has%20come%20for%20policy%20to%20adjust%2C%26quot%3B%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20during%20his%20address%20at%20a%20gathering%20of%20central%20bankers%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-are-coming-federal-reserve-jackson-hole-powell-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJackson%20Hole%2C%20Wyoming%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month.%20%26quot%3BThe%20direction%20of%20travel%20is%20clear%2C%20and%20the%20timing%20and%20pace%20of%20rate%20cuts%20will%20depend%20on%20incoming%20data%2C%20the%20evolving%20outlook%2C%20and%20the%20balance%20of%20risks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-august-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-rate-cuts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20inflation%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edata%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20came%20out%20last%20Wednesday%20was%20the%20last%20large%20piece%20of%20data%20before%20the%20Fed%20meeting.%20With%20August's%20core%20CPI%20coming%20in%20unexpectedly%20hotter%20than%20expected%2C%20it%20was%20looking%20likely%20a%2050-basis-point%20cut%20wouldn't%20happen.%20That's%20because%20a%20larger%20rate%20cut%20makes%20borrowing%20cheaper%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20drive%20up%20spending%20and%20fuel%20price%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-interest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-recession-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20supports%20a%20rate%20cut%20this%20month%20%E2%80%94%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20ticked%20down%20in%20August%20but%20stayed%20above%20its%20recent%20lows%2C%20and%20hiring%20gains%20have%20cooled.%20Lower%20rates%20ease%20pressure%20on%20companies'%20bottom%20lines%2C%20freeing%20up%20budgets%20for%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20economists%20hope%20that%20the%20long-sought%20soft%20landing%20of%20getting%20inflation%20under%20control%20while%20avoiding%20a%20devastating%20recession%20could%20be%20near.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20rate%20cut%20is%20great%20news%20for%20middle-class%20families%2C%20not%20only%20does%20it%20underscore%20the%20Fed%20is%20convinced%20that%20inflation%20is%20coming%20under%20control%2C%20it%20signals%20the%20economy%20has%20recovered%20to%20a%20faster%2C%20sustainable%20growth%20trajectory%20and%20is%20ready%20for%20further%20investments%20in%20job%20creation%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Madowitz%2C%20the%20former%20director%20of%20macroeconomic%20policy%20at%20the%20Washington%20Center%20for%20Equitable%20Growth%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d213ed81-690b-4194-9569-8ae1349857cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt'll%20take%20time%20for%20the%20cuts%20to%20set%20in%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlena%20McTier%2C%20a%20Gen%20Zer%2C%20had%20been%20looking%20to%20replace%20the%20car%20she%20purchased%20in%202017%20this%20summer%2C%20but%20she%20was%20up%20against%20sticker%20shock.%20She%20can't%20wait%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhen-is-the-next-fed-meeting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20to%20announce%20rate%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she's%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcar-prices-falling-forecast-outlook-new-used-electric-vehicle-market-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eholding%20on%20to%20her%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Buntil%20a%20solid%20decision%20is%20made%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20on%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20are%20cut%2C%20I%20am%20going%20to%20actively%20explore%20the%20different%20rates%20that%20are%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20McTier%2C%20who%20is%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20used%20vehicle%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20take%20a%20while%20for%20McTier%20to%20see%20those%20lower%20rates.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20will%20be%20immediately%20impacted%2C%20there%20will%20still%20be%20a%20lag%20for%20relief%20in%20some%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20fact%20that%20monetary%20policy%20does%20take%20time%20to%20work%20its%20way%20through%20the%20system%2C%20it'll%20be%20the%20same%20to%20some%20degree%20with%20the%20rate%20reductions%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Hamrick%2C%20senior%20economic%20analyst%20for%20Bankrate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20added%20that%20prime%20lending%20rates%20will%20likely%20be%20adjusted%20soon%20after%20the%20decision%3A%20%26quot%3BBanks%20adjust%20their%20prime%20lending%20rates%2C%20the%20rates%20reserved%20for%20their%20best%20customers%2C%20and%20those%20tend%20to%20then%20be%20reflected%20in%20credit%20card%20rates%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamrick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECredit%20card%20interest%20rates%20have%20been%20at%20historic%20highs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fblog%2Fcredit-card-interest-rate-margins-at-all-time-high%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20found%20that%20the%20average%20annual%20percentage%20rate%20on%20credit%20cards%20has%20almost%20doubled%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20to%2022.8%25%20in%202023.%20However%2C%20the%20lag%20means%20that%20those%20hoping%20to%20pay%20off%20credit%20cards%20won't%20be%20materially%20impacted%20by%20this%20month's%20rate%20cut%20%E2%80%94%20it'll%20take%20time%20for%20the%20relief%20to%20set%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERate%20cuts%20will%20also%20eventually%20make%20it%20cheaper%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-small-business