een%20Larry%20Page's%20life%20and%20finances%20since%202012%2C%20as%20head%20of%20the%20Google%20founder's%20family%20fund.%3Cp%3EDre%20Waltizer%3B%20Jeff%20Chiu%2FAP%20Photo%3B%20Google%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20a%20New%20York%20developer%20was%20in%20negotiations%20to%20buy%20two%20pristine%20islands%20in%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20a%20mile%20north%20of%20St.%20Thomas.%20He%20had%20made%20an%20offer%20of%20%249%20million%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20had%20hit%20a%20snag.%20Suddenly%2C%20out%20of%20nowhere%2C%20a%20mysterious%20company%20based%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20California%2C%20swooped%20in%20and%20snapped%20up%20both%20islands%20for%20%2423%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20developer%20was%20furious.%20Suspecting%20double-dealing%2C%20he%20went%20to%20court%20to%20contest%20the%20sale.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20way%20to%20tell%20who%20was%20behind%20the%20sudden%20purchase.%20The%20buyer%20was%20hidden%20behind%20a%20web%20of%20limited-liability%20companies%2C%20a%20business%20structure%20that%20allows%20owners%20to%20remain%20shielded%20from%20view.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20took%20months%20of%20litigation%20before%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20LLCs%20was%20revealed%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20cofounder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-page-google-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELarry%20Page%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20documents%20relating%20to%20the%20deal%20mentioned%20Page%20by%20name.%20His%20connection%20was%20confirmed%20only%20after%20lawyers%20for%20the%20developer%20were%20able%20to%20question%20another%20man%2C%20Wayne%20Osborne%2C%20who%20has%20overseen%20Page's%20life%20and%20finances%20since%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-offices-wealth-management-secrets-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKoop%2C%20Page's%20family%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Osborne%20has%20shrouded%20his%20employer%20in%20a%20level%20of%20privacy%20that's%20nearly%20unparalleled%20in%20the%20modern%20era%20%E2%80%94%20keeping%20Page's%20name%20out%20of%20business%20documents%2C%20court%20records%2C%20and%20news%20headlines.%20To%20purchase%20the%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cofounder-larry-page-private-islands-carribean-south-pacific-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eislands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20came%20out%20during%20Osborne's%20deposition%2C%20Koop%20set%20up%20the%20LLC%20with%20the%20express%20aim%20of%20obscuring%20any%20link%20to%20Page.%20When%20Osborne%20does%20his%20job%2C%20it's%20almost%20impossible%20to%20detect%20that%20Page%20%E2%80%94%20or%20Osborne%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20was%20even%20there.%20%26quot%3BWayne%20operates%20in%20the%20shadows%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20an%20industry%20peer%20who%20knows%20Osborne%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Osborne%20at%20the%20head%20of%20Page's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-family-office-guide-advisors-consultants-accountants-lawyers-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20special%20breed%20of%20private%20wealth-management%20firms%20that%20advise%20the%20ultrarich%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20world's%20go-to%20search%20engine%20has%20become%20a%20model%20of%20inaccessibility.%20The%20world's%20sixth-richest%20man%2C%20estimated%20to%20be%20worth%20%24143%20billion%2C%20Page%20is%20almost%20never%20interviewed%20or%20photographed.%20Last%20year%2C%20when%20lawyers%20sought%20to%20question%20him%20about%20his%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epossible%20business%20ties%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-chase-drawn-out-breakup-with-jeffrey-epstein-2023-6%3Futm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_campaign%3Dbusiness-sf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20financier%20and%20child%20predator%2C%20investigators%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F05%2F04%2Fgoogle-co-founder-larry-page-can-get-jeffrey-epstein-case-service.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunable%20to%20find%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20address%20for%20Page%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20subpoena%20him.%20When%20he%20flies%2C%20his%20private%20jets%20copy%20the%20%26quot%3BQS%26quot%3B%20configuration%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-jet-charters-cheaper-with-empty-leg-flights-ceo-says-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetJets%3C%2Fa%3E%20uses%20on%20its%20tail%20numbers%2C%20to%20throw%20off%20suspicion%20that%20Page%20might%20be%20aboard.%20The%20creator%20of%20Gmail%20even%20avoids%20using%20his%20own%20product.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20you%20speak%20to%20Wayne%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20someone%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20both%20Page%20and%20Osborne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsborne's%20association%20with%20Page%20has%20given%20him%20a%20revered%20status%20in%20the%20world%20of%20family%20officers.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20wants%20to%20connect%20with%20Wayne%20because%20he's%20connected%20to%20Larry%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one%20former%20Osborne%20employee.%20His%20success%20has%20also%20helped%20fuel%20a%20boom%20in%20family%20offices%2C%20a%20financial%20structure%20pioneered%20by%20J.P.%20Morgan%20and%20popularized%20by%20the%20Rockefellers.%20Today%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20family%20offices%20globally%2C%20with%20the%20total%20number%20tripling%20between%202019%20and%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%20provider%20Preqin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20in%20a%20surprising%20move%2C%20the%20man%20who%20has%20enabled%20Page%20to%20live%20in%20the%20shadows%20is%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20shadows%20himself.%20Osborne%20is%20seeking%20to%20parlay%20his%20proximity%20to%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20secretive%20tech%20founders%20into%20a%20rapidly%20growing%20side%20hustle.%20His%20new%20company%2C%20Way2B1%2C%20has%20developed%20software%20that%20essentially%20creates%20a%20digital%20version%20of%20Osborne%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20can%20put%20his%20trade%20secrets%20to%20work%20for%20other%20investors.%20Insiders%20say%20Osborne%20has%20boasted%20that%20Way2B1%20is%20already%20working%20with%20more%20than%20100%20high-net-worth%20families%2C%20and%20that%20Morgan%20Stanley%20has%20signed%20a%20lucrative%20deal%20with%20the%20company%20giving%20it%20access%20to%20the%20bank's%20high-net-worth%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20company%2C%20is%20to%20dominate%20the%20world%20of%20wealth%20management%20the%20way%20Page%20monopolized%20online%20search.%20%26quot%3BWayne%20wants%20to%20create%20the%20Google%20of%20family%20offices%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20Way2B1%20employee%20says.%20It%20is%20also%20closely%20intertwined%20with%20Koop%2C%20as%20some%20staffers%20have%20moved%20between%20the%20family%20office%20and%20Osborne's%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Larry%20Page%20on%20stage%20talking%20through%20a%20microphone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d0a46643b5e59d16b69e31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222057%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPage%20is%20famously%20private%2C%20even%20by%20the%20standards%20of%20tech%20founders.%20He%20stopped%20presenting%20at%20Google%20product%20launches%20and%20earnings%20calls%20in%202013%20and%20hasn't%20attended%20a%20press%20conference%20since%202015.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20ambitious%20new%20venture%20comes%20with%20an%20inherent%20tension.%20To%20protect%20Page%2C%20Osborne%20has%20long%20remained%20hidden%2C%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20megabillionaire's%20curtain.%20But%20unlike%20Koop%2C%20Way2B1%20is%20a%20for-profit%20business%20that%20needs%20to%20attract%20clients%20and%20make%20money.%20%26quot%3BWayne%20advertises%20for%20Way2B1%20by%20talking%20about%20it%20with%20everyone%20he%20talks%20to%20in%20the%20course%20of%20his%20work%20with%20Koop%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20highly%20overlapping%20jobs.%26quot%3B%20As%20Osborne%20has%20taken%20on%20the%20role%20of%20salesman%2C%20venturing%20into%20the%20world%20to%20promote%20his%20enterprise%2C%20he%20has%20confronted%20an%20uncomfortable%20dilemma%3A%20How%20do%20you%20safeguard%20the%20privacy%20of%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20richest%20men%20while%20hawking%20the%20secrets%20to%20his%20success%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20run%20their%20family%20offices%2C%20most%20tech%20titans%20rely%20on%20former%20wealth%20managers%20and%20business-school%20alumni.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsergey-brin-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESergey%20Brin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20cofounded%20Google%20with%20Page%2C%20employs%20George%20Pavlov%2C%20a%20former%20venture%20capitalist.%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20leans%20on%20Iconiq%20Capital%2C%20a%20financial-services%20firm.%20Jeff%20Bezos%20looks%20to%20Melinda%20Lewison%2C%20a%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20grad%20and%20former%20financial%20analyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsborne%20started%20his%20career%20not%20in%20finance%20but%20in%20faith.%20Born%20in%20Mississippi%2C%20he%20graduated%20from%20Princeton%20Theological%20Seminary%20with%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20divinity.%20But%20Osborne%2C%20who%20identified%20as%20gay%2C%20soon%20found%20himself%20ostracized%20by%20his%20own%20church.%20In%201997%2C%20three%20years%20after%20he%20was%20ordained%20as%20a%20Presbyterian%20elder%2C%20the%20church%20tightened%20its%20rules%20blocking%20gays%20and%20lesbians%20from%20serving%20as%20elders%2C%20ministers%2C%20and%20deacons.%20When%20two%20church%20members%20objected%20to%20Osborne%20serving%20on%20the%20governing%20body%20of%20his%20Connecticut%20church%2C%20the%20case%20went%20to%20an%20ecclesiastical%20court.%20After%20a%20high-profile%20battle%2C%20Osborne%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20victory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nydailynews.com%2F1999%2F01%2F16%2Fdivision-in-the-ranks-gay-lesbian-issue-splits-presbyterians%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereverberated%20through%20Presbyterian%20congregations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20refusal%20to%20answer%20questions%20from%20church%20leaders%20about%20his%20sexual%20activity%20with%20his%20partner%20garnered%20national%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1999%2F03%2F08%2Fnyregion%2Fgay-man-is-allowed-to-be-a-church-leader.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheadlines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20an%20appropriate%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained%20to%20reporters%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20something%20%26quot%3Beven%20my%20best%20friends%20don't%20ask%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20gave%20Osborne%20a%20taste%20of%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20to%20have%20your%20private%20affairs%20thrust%20into%20the%20national%20spotlight.%20And%20his%20industry%20peers%20say%20the%20ministry%2C%20with%20its%20emphasis%20on%20service%20to%20others%2C%20is%20not%20unlike%20the%20role%20of%20a%20family%20officer.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20say%20it's%20almost%20an%20ideal%20background%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Natasha%20Pearl%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Aston%20Pearl%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm%20that%20works%20with%20family%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221513%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wayne%20Osborne%20embraces%20people%20at%20a%20church.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d0a4f11d8d2deb96b75159%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22995%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOsborne%20was%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20dispute%20over%20gay%20rights%20in%20the%20Presbyterian%20Church%20in%20the%20late%201990s.%20The%20episode%20gave%20him%20an%20early%20taste%20of%20being%20thrust%20into%20the%20national%20spotlight.%3Cp%3EJames%20Estrin%2FThe%20New%20York%20Times%2FRedux%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20Osborne%20was%20standing%20up%20to%20the%20church%2C%20he%20was%20discovering%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20ministry.%20Back%20in%20his%20late%2020s%2C%20he%20landed%20a%20job%20as%20an%20assistant%20to%20Helen%20Frankenthaler%2C%20the%20celebrated%20painter.%20He%20paid%20her%20bills%2C%20handled%20her%20publicity%2C%20and%20helped%20her%20manage%20her%20art%20inventory.%20%26quot%3BI%20found%20that%20I%20have%20a%20knack%20for%20helping%20people%20manage%20their%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Osborne%20said%20in%20a%20podcast%20with%20the%20investment%20firm%20Minerva%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20found%20he%20could%20sympathize%20with%20the%20stress%20that%20comes%20from%20having%20someone%20else%20manage%20your%20wealth.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20turning%20over%20your%20life%2C%20or%20control%20of%20parts%20of%20your%20life%2C%20over%20to%20these%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20Minerva%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BIt%20creates%20an%20opportunity%20for%20anxiety%20and%20worry.%20Are%20they%20going%20to%20spend%20money%20the%20way%20I'd%20want%20them%20to%20spend%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20A%20client's%20feeling%20toward%20the%20wealth%20manager%20becomes%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you%20because%20I%20need%20you%2C%20and%20I%20hate%20you%20because%20I%20need%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20podcast%20appearance%20was%20a%20departure%20for%20Osborne.%20The%20role%20of%20a%20family%20officer%20is%20not%20only%20to%20keep%20your%20client%20out%20of%20the%20spotlight%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20spotlight%20yourself.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20appearing%20on%20the%20show%20gave%20Osborne%20an%20opportunity%20to%20talk%20up%20Way2B1.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20build%20the%20best%20tech%20in%20the%20world%20for%20family%20offices%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled%20telling%20his%20employers.%20During%20his%20spiel%2C%20he%20was%20careful%20not%20to%20mention%20either%20Page%20or%20Koop%20by%20name%2C%20referring%20only%20to%20his%20work%20for%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20tech%20families%20here%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Frankenthaler%2C%20Osborne%20went%20to%20work%20for%20the%20retail%20executive%20Joseph%20E.%20Brooks%2C%20whose%20family%20oversaw%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20Lord%20%26amp%3B%20Taylor%20department%20store.%20In%202000%2C%20he%20began%20working%20for%20the%20news%20tycoon%20Mortimer%20Zuckerman.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wasn't%20real%20tech-savvy%2C%26quot%3B%20Osborne%20told%20the%20Minerva%20podcast.%20But%20Zuckerman%20appreciated%20the%20innovative%20approach%20Osborne%20brought%20to%20his%20personal%20affairs%20and%20his%20business%20empire%2C%20which%20included%20U.S.%20News%20and%20World%20Report%20and%20Boston%20Properties.%20One%20idea%20Osborne%20implemented%20was%20a%20sort%20of%20early%20version%20of%20Google%20Docs.%20Called%20%26quot%3Bthe%20phone%20list%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20allowed%20an%20employee%20at%20any%20of%20Zuckerman's%20far-flung%20properties%20to%20leave%20a%20comment%20that%20the%20entire%20staff%20could%20see%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20moved%20up%20the%20ladder%20of%20high-net-worth%20individuals%2C%20Osborne%20caught%20the%20eye%20of%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20of%20them%20all.%20In%202012%2C%20he%20moved%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%20to%20run%20the%20family%20office%20for%20Page%2C%20who%20was%20in%20a%20period%20of%20transition.%20Page%20had%20just%20been%20reinstated%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20of%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he'd%20later%20oversee%20the%20creation%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-alphabet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparent%20company%2C%20Alphabet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20restructuring%20was%20widely%20seen%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20retirement%20plan%20for%20Page%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20retain%20a%20controlling%20stake%20in%20the%20company%20while%20stepping%20away%20from%20direct%20responsibility.%20Page%2C%20who'd%20revealed%20he%20had%20a%20condition%20that%20led%20to%20paralysis%20in%20his%20vocal%20cords%2C%20stopped%20presenting%20at%20product%20launches%20and%20earnings%20calls%20in%202013.%20He%20has%20not%20attended%20a%20press%20conference%20since%202015%2C%20the%20year%20Alphabet%20was%20launched.%20He%20was%20becoming%20Google's%20invisible%20man%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Osborne%20was%20there%20to%20help%20orchestrate%20the%20disappearing%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EKoop's%20headquarters%20sits%20just%20off%20coastal%20Highway%20101%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20tucked%20discreetly%20between%20a%20Starbucks%20and%20a%20Shell%20gas%20station.%20From%20the%20family%20office's%20nerve%20center%2C%20Osborne%20oversees%20a%20complex%20maze%20of%20LLCs%2C%20financial%20advisors%2C%20and%20interpersonal%20dynamics.%20Like%20Osborne%2C%20Koop's%20staff%20is%20fiercely%20committed%20to%20Page's%20privacy.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20relatively%20small%20group%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ken%20Goldman%2C%20who%20ran%20the%20family%20office%20for%20the%20former%20Google%20CEO%20Eric%20Schmidt%20and%20occasionally%20met%20with%20Osborne%20to%20discuss%20a%20fleet%20of%20private%20jets%20the%20two%20billionaires%20shared.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20detail-oriented.%20They%20watch%20their%20money%20carefully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headquarters%20of%20Koop.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d0a55d392a3bda9f232f79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20small%20staff%20at%20Koop%2C%20Page's%20family%20office%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20are%20fiercely%20committed%20to%20Page's%20privacy.%20%3Cp%3EHugh%20Langley%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20keeping%20with%20their%20mission%2C%20most%20of%20Koop's%20staffers%20are%20vague%20about%20their%20work%20histories%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20LinkedIn%20pages.%20Before%20joining%20the%20family%20office%2C%20they're%20required%20to%20sign%20nondisclosure%20agreements%2C%20and%20background%20checks%20can%20be%20repeated%20annually.%20One%20person%20Osborne%20has%20leaned%20on%20for%20protecting%20Koop's%20security%2C%20according%20to%20two%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20process%2C%20is%20Michael%20Floyd%2C%20a%20former%20CIA%20officer%20and%20an%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fexcerpt-phil-houston-michael-floyd-susan-carniceros-spy-lie-flna892290%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpy%20the%20Lie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20training%20manual%20for%20spotting%20deception.%20Floyd%2C%20says%20someone%20who%20knows%20him%2C%20is%20Osborne's%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20lie%20detector%2C%26quot%3B%20using%20his%20expertise%20in%20espionage%20to%20identify%20anything%20that%20could%20threaten%20the%20privacy%20and%20sanctity%20of%20PageWorld.%20Sometimes%2C%20as%20Osborne%20explained%20on%20the%20Minerva%20podcast%2C%20%26quot%3Byour%20weakest%20link%20is%20from%20within.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefitting%20its%20billionaire%20tech-founder%20boss%2C%20Koop%20has%20an%20impressive%20fleet%20of%20engineers%20working%20on%20the%20Page%20family's%20enterprises%2C%20assets%2C%20and%20philanthropic%20interests.%20Under%20Osborne's%20supervision%2C%20Koop%20collaborated%20with%20Composite%20Energy%20Technologies%20to%20build%20an%20electro-foiling%20catamaran%2C%20a%2037-foot%20vessel%20designed%20to%20glide%20over%20the%20water%20at%20impressive%20speeds%20with%20little%20human%20control%20and%2C%20in%20time%2C%20zero%20emissions.%20(A%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20project%20says%20the%20catamaran%20belongs%20to%20Page.)%20Koop%20also%20formed%20an%20LLC%20for%20Oceankind%2C%20the%20marine-conservation%20charity%20run%20by%20Page's%20wife%2C%20Lucy%20Southworth%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20track%20the%20millions%20of%20dollars%20flowing%20through%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20insular%20world%20of%20family%20offices%2C%20Koop%20has%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20well-run%20enterprise%20that's%20not%20allergic%20to%20a%20little%20fun.%20According%20to%20one%20person%20who%20attended%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eparticularly%20memorable%20Mardi%20Gras-themed%20party%20for%20Koop%20employees%20and%20trusted%20industry%20friends%20held%20at%20Nola%2C%20a%20Creole%20restaurant%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20a%20live%20alligator%20hung%20out%20on%20the%20bar.%20(A%20representative%20for%20Osborne%20denied%20this%20happened.)%20Osborne%20himself%20is%20seen%20as%20charismatic%2C%20friendly%2C%20and%20a%20sharp%20dresser.%20%26quot%3BAlways%20good%20shoes%2C%20good%20jeans%2C%20good%20jackets%2C%26quot%3B%20someone%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20him%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20takes%20care%20of%20himself%20really%20well%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsborne%20can%20also%20be%20oddly%20finicky%2C%20those%20who%20know%20him%20say%2C%20insisting%20on%20things%20being%20just%20the%20way%20he%20wants%20them.%20One%20person%20who%20dined%20out%20with%20Osborne%20recalls%20watching%20him%20recoil%20when%20his%20dish%20arrived.%20Apparently%20displeased%20with%20the%20chef's%20architectural%20plating%20concept%2C%20he%20sent%20the%20dish%20back%20and%20ordered%20that%20the%20food%20be%20laid%20out%20flat%20on%20his%20plate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPage%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story%2C%20and%20Osborne%20issued%20a%20short%20statement.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20that%20Business%20Insider's%20goal%20is%20to%20create%20a%20sensationalized%2C%20misleading%20article%20that%20falls%20short%20of%20responsible%20journalism%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads.%20%26quot%3BAnyone%20familiar%20with%20the%20individuals%20mentioned%20in%20your%20article%20will%20recognize%20how%20inaccurate%20your%20story%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20befitting%20his%20role%20at%20Koop%2C%20Osborne's%20public%20profile%20is%20limited%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20few%20public%20photos%20of%20him%20is%20the%20headshot%20on%20Way2B1's%20website.%20But%20he%20reveals%20bits%20of%20himself%20on%20his%20personal%20Tumblr.%20One%20tab%20contains%20a%20humorous%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwayneosborne.tumblr.com%2FPresidential%2520Platform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresidential%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20ideas%20ranging%20from%20the%20sweet%20(%26quot%3BThe%20elderly%20will%20be%20interviewed%2C%20their%20thoughts%20and%20wisdom%20recorded%20for%20posterity%26quot%3B)%20to%20the%20silly%20(%26quot%3BEvery%20citizen%20will%20receive%20a%20free%20margarita%20(frozen%20or%20on%20the%20rocks)%20after%20more%20than%208%20hours%20of%20work%26quot%3B)%20to%20the%20impossible%20(%26quot%3BAll%20days%20will%20have%2012%20hours%20of%20sunshine%26quot%3B).%20In%20another%20list%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BMy%2055%20Ways%20to%20be%20Satisfied%2C%26quot%3B%20Osborne%20starts%20with%20%26quot%3Bhave%20good%20morning%20workouts%26quot%3B%20before%20proceeding%20through%20%26quot%3Bwrite%20poetry%2C%20draw%20objects%2C%20paint%20canvas%2C%20and%20read%20a%20good%20book%26quot%3B%20(No.%2010)%2C%20%26quot%3Bhave%20a%20good%20bedtime%20tea%20every%20night%26quot%3B%20(No.%2019)%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bvote%20in%20every%20election%26quot%3B%20(No.%2051).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20for%20Way2B1%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20tech-forward%20approach%20Osborne%20brought%20to%20his%20role%20at%20Koop.%20When%20he%20took%20over%20Page's%20family%20office%2C%20he%20was%20bothered%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20was%20no%20tech%20platform%20designed%20to%20manage%20the%20increasingly%20complex%20lives%20of%20wealthy%20families.%20So%20he%20told%20his%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20presumably%20Page%20and%20Southworth%2C%20though%20he%20avoids%20mentioning%20them%20%E2%80%94%20about%20a%20concept%20he%20had%20raised%20with%20Mortimer%20Zuckerman%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20if%2C%20with%20one%20username%20and%20password%2C%20you%20could%20access%20your%20whole%20world%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Osborne%20proposed%20developing%20the%20tech%20on%20his%20own.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20like%20to%20set%20up%20a%20company.%20I%20don't%20want%20you%20investing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20family.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you'll%20get%20out%20of%20this%20is%20you'll%20get%20the%20most%20advanced%20family%20office%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%20His%20employers%20told%20him%20to%20go%20for%20it.%20They%20were%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bvery%20supportive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Osborne%20tells%20it%2C%20he%20had%20been%20developing%20the%20Way2B1%20software%20for%20about%20a%20year%20when%20his%20employers%20suggested%20it%20was%20time%20to%20talk.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20a%20little%20nervous%2C%20to%20be%20honest%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20Minerva%20podcast.%20But%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20family%20was%20thrilled.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20changed%20our%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20given%20us%20peace%20of%20mind.%20Will%20you%20let%20us%20invest%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20insight%20behind%20Way2B1%20is%20that%20the%20secrecy%20inherent%20in%20family%20offices%20and%20the%20insularity%20of%20their%20small%20teams%20have%20actually%20put%20the%20wealthy%20at%20a%20disadvantage.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20family%20is%20reinventing%20the%20wheel%20for%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Osborne%20says.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20families%20are%20making%20really%20big%20mistakes%20because%20they're%20building%20this%20thing%20from%20scratch.%26quot%3B%20By%20downloading%20the%20industry's%20best%20practices%20into%20a%20single%20platform%2C%20Osborne%20is%20following%20Big%20Tech's%20playbook%3A%20Start%20by%20testing%20your%20idea%20in%20beta%2C%20then%20roll%20it%20out%20to%20a%20wider%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWay2B1%2C%20which%20Osborne%20calls%20%26quot%3Bthe%20new%20paradigm%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20essentially%20a%20fancy%20task-management%20system%2C%20designed%20to%20ensure%20investments%20are%20vetted%2C%20LLCs%20are%20set%20up%2C%20nannies%20are%20paid%2C%20and%20property%20repairs%20are%20done%20on%20time.%20The%20idea%20is%20that%20the%20family%20principals%20and%20family-office%20coordinators%20can%20see%20everything%20in%20one%20place%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20approve%20purchases%2C%20green%20light%20investments%2C%20and%20ensure%20background%20checks%20are%20completed%2C%20all%20protected%20with%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.way2b1.com%2Fsecurity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWay2B1%20likes%20to%20boast%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20same%20encryption%20services%20used%20by%20the%20US%20government.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20Osborne%20sees%20Way2B1%20as%20a%20means%20of%20helping%20other%20family%20offices%20build%20themselves%20in%20Koop's%20image%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20think%20it's%20important%20that%20families%20have%20privacy%2C%20that%20they%20keep%20their%20teams%20small.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Koop%20and%20Way2B1%20have%20seemingly%20been%20intertwined%20from%20the%20outset%2C%20Osborne%20has%20erected%20some%20internal%20walls.%20For%20starters%2C%20not%20everyone%20who%20works%20at%20Way2B1%20knows%20that%20their%20CEO%20also%20runs%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20lucrative%20family%20offices.%20%26quot%3BJust%20being%20there%20isn't%20enough%20to%20grant%20you%20access%20to%20those%20circles%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20says.%20When%20Koop%20is%20mentioned%20at%20Way2B1%2C%20it's%20referred%20to%20by%20its%20code%20name%3A%20Taurus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20connections%20between%20the%20two%20firms%20run%20deep.%20Osborne%20has%20hired%20former%20Koop%20employees%20for%20his%20side%20hustle%2C%20and%20he%20sometimes%20solicits%20feedback%20from%20Koop%20employees%20on%20Way2B1%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20ties%20to%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investment%20from%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20richest%20men%2C%20Way2B1%20remains%20lean%2C%20with%20fewer%20than%20100%20employees.%20And%20even%20though%20it's%20been%20around%20for%20less%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20insiders%20say%20it's%20already%20been%20through%20at%20least%20one%20round%20of%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Way2B1%20employees%20resent%20what%20they%20see%20as%20Osborne's%20unquestioning%20fealty%20to%20Page.%20%26quot%3BHe%20thinks%20Larry%20has%20his%20money%20by%20divine%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20says.%20They%20worry%20that%20for%20Osborne%2C%20Page%20will%20always%20come%20first%2C%20and%20Way2B1%20a%20distant%20second.%20%26quot%3BAny%20chance%20he'd%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20former%20employee%20recalls%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe'd%20brag%20about%20how%20much%20his%20Pixel%20phone%20was%20better%20than%20the%20iPhone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20white%20yacht%20is%20seen%20moving%20through%20the%20water.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d78384289b805d1db3e26d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPage%20bought%20the%20superyacht%20Senses%20in%202011%20for%20%2445%20million.%20His%20lifestyle%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20private%20islands%20he%20has%20purchased%20%E2%80%94%20are%20often%20shielded%20by%20the%20family%20office%20overseen%20by%20Osborne.%3Cp%3EGilles%20Martin-Raget%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20tensions%20have%20forced%20Osborne%20to%20perform%20a%20delicate%20juggling%20act.%20Way2B1%20isn't%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town%2C%20and%20it's%20competing%20with%20a%20host%20of%20other%20software%20systems%20being%20shopped%20around%20the%20world%20of%20family%20offices.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Ffrancoisbotha%2F2023%2F10%2F31%2Fthe-2023-family-office-software-roundup%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForbes%20keeps%20a%20running%20list%20of%20some%20of%20the%20best%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eindustry%20insiders%20mentioned%20Nines%20and%20Summitas%20as%20two%20favorites.%20That%20means%20Osborne%20needs%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20spread%20the%20word%20about%20his%20product%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20how%20it%20builds%20on%20the%20expertise%20he%20has%20honed%20in%20Page's%20service%2C%20without%20subjecting%20his%20boss%20to%20unwanted%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20public%2C%20the%20separation%20between%20Way2B1%20and%20Page's%20family%20fund%20has%20proved%20difficult%20to%20navigate.%20In%20June%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWay2B1's%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20Hal%20Bailey%2C%20a%20former%20director%20at%20Google%2C%20spoke%20at%20a%20conference%20touting%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWay2B1's%20technology.%20To%20demonstrate%20its%20effectiveness%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20how%20the%20software%20had%20helped%20one%20client%20navigate%20the%20complex%20web%20of%20global%20bureaucracy%20and%20donate%20supplies%20to%20a%20cluster%20of%20islands%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID%20pandemic.%20To%20anyone%20paying%20attention%2C%20it%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20reference%20to%20donations%20Page%20made%20in%20July%202021%2C%20soon%20after%20his%20purchase%20of%20a%20Fijian%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20strange%20thing%20for%20Way2B1%20to%20brag%20about%2C%20given%20the%20controversy%20sparked%20by%20Page's%20donation.%20After%20Fijian%20broadcasters%20revealed%20that%20Page%20was%20behind%20the%20supplies%2C%20Fijian%20health%20authorities%20ordered%20them%20to%20take%20down%20the%20story.%20The%20censorship%2C%20first%20reported%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20unleashed%20a%20wave%20of%20bad%20press%20for%20Fiji%2C%20which%20had%20allowed%20billionaires%20like%20Page%20to%20slip%20past%20its%20closed%20borders%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cofounder-larry-page-sold-superyacht-senses-fiji-yacht-billionaire-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuperyachts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20private%20jets.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20the%20government%20of%20New%20Zealand%20was%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle-9863993%2FBillionaire-Google-founder-Larry-Page-allowed-enter-New-Zealand-Fijian-island.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadmit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Page's%2012-year-old%20son%20had%20been%20evacuated%20from%20Fiji%20and%20brought%20to%20New%20Zealand%20for%20medical%20treatment%20even%20as%20its%20own%20citizens%20were%20barred%20from%20returning%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Way2B1%20to%20let%20slip%20a%20story%20about%20Page's%20generosity%20wasn't%20necessarily%20the%20worst%20thing%20in%20the%20world.%20And%20it's%20possible%20the%20anecdote%20was%20shared%20with%20Page's%20blessing.%20But%20whether%20Page%20likes%20it%20or%20not%2C%20Osborne's%20new%20venture%20is%20bringing%20fresh%20attention%20to%20his%20personal%20affairs.%20Through%20his%20investment%20in%20Way2B1%2C%20Page%20is%20seeking%20to%20make%20money%20by%20monetizing%20the%20techniques%20he%20uses%20to%20make%20money.%20And%20that%2C%20inevitably%2C%20is%20going%20to%20thrust%20him%20into%20the%20limelight%20he%20has%20spent%20so%20dearly%20to%20avoid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fhugh-langley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHugh%20Langley%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20c