professors%2C%20and%20it%20offered%20me%20an%20opportunity%20as%20a%20TA%2C%20so%20the%20decision%20was%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20teaching%20assistantship%20paid%20for%20all%20my%20tuition%20and%20also%20paid%20me%20around%20%2420%2C000%20each%20semester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9fdec8c-c770-4f06-a7af-8a6bb5f26c51%5C%22%3EI%20started%20applying%20for%20jobs%20in%202017%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20must've%20applied%20for%20over%20100%20of%20them.%20When%20you%20apply%2C%20employers%20ask%20you%20if%20they'll%20need%20to%20sponsor%20you%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20future%2C%20as%20not%20every%20employer%20can%20cover%20the%20financial%20costs%20associated%20with%20the%20process%20when%20the%20time%20comes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20four%20offers%20from%20Microsoft%2C%20Verizon%2C%20Deutsche%20Bank%2C%20and%20Disney.%20Microsoft%20had%20the%20best%20offer%20and%20was%20willing%20to%20sponsor%20my%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a93721cf-c9e0-46f2-bd96-3071c98b4800%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20with%20Microsoft%20in%202018%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20my%20job%20at%20Microsoft%20in%20Seattle%2C%20I%20could%20work%20thanks%20to%20a%20student%20work%20permit%20that%20lasts%20one%20year%20after%20graduation%20and%20is%20granted%20to%20all%20F-1%20visa%20students.%20While%20working%20on%20the%20student%20permit%2C%20your%20employer%20helps%20you%20apply%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh1b-visa-lottery-changes-benefit-startups-hiring-immigrants-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH-1B%3C%2Fa%3E%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-green-card-applications-pause-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreen%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20working%20on%20my%20H-1B%20visa%20for%20a%20year.%20By%20this%20point%2C%20I%20had%20lived%20in%20the%20US%20for%20abou