0rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FLobzang-Chorol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20when%20the%20challenges%20seemed%20overwhelming%20%E2%80%94%20from%20people%20unwilling%20to%20give%20their%20borewell%20water%20samples%20to%20collecting%20secondary%20baseline%20data%20and%20the%20emotional%20weight%20of%20seeing%20the%20deterioration%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20water%20resources%20firsthand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20every%20time%20I%20felt%20discouraged%2C%20I%20remembered%20the%20faces%20of%20my%20family%20and%20community%20back%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20depending%20on%20this%20precious%20resource.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20academic%20research%3B%20it%20was%20about%20the%20lives%20and%20futures%20of%20real%20people.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20earning%20a%20degree%3B%20it%20was%20about%20securing%20a%20sustainable%20future%20for%20Ladakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20invisible%20network%20of%20underground%20aquifers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeh%20is%20a%20town%20nestled%20in%20the%20rain%20shadow%20area%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F312359%2Fscientist-innovates-solar-hamam-warm-water-heater-for-thousands-in-himachal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emighty%20Himalayas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20receiving%20barely%20100%20mm%20of%20annual%20rainfall.%20Life%20in%20this%20high-altitude%20desert%20thrives%20against%20all%20odds%2C%20thanks%20to%20an%20invisible%20network%20of%20underground%20aquifers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20aquifers%20are%20essentially%20natural%20underground%20reservoirs%20formed%20in%20the%20porous%20layers%20of%20rock%20and%20sediment%20beneath%20Leh.%20They%20are%20recharged%20primarily%20by%20snowmelt%20from%20surrounding%20mountains%2C%20glacial%20melt%20from%20nearby%20glaciers%2C%20limited%20annual%20rainfall%2C%20and%20infiltration%20from%20rivers%20and%20streams.%20This%20recharge%20process%20is%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20seasonal%20patterns%2C%20with%20most%20occurring%20during%20the%20warmer%20months%20when%20snow%20and%20glaciers%20melt%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20aquifers%20act%20as%20a%20natural%20storage%20and%20filtration%20system%2C%20holding%20water%20that%20percolates%20through%20the%20ground%20and%20releasing%20it%20slowly%20over%20time.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20groundwater%20maintains%20a%20relatively%20stable%20temperature%2C%20which%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20both%20ecosystems%20and%20human%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20920px)%20100vw%2C%20920px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh's%20groundwater%20gets%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%20920w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-500x268.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-768x412.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-150x81.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365887%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20underground%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%20and%20glacial%20melt.%20(Image%20courtesy%3A%20Reach%20Ladakh)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20way%20these%20aquifers%20support%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20thriving%20is%20multifaceted.%20They%20sustain%20natural%20vegetation%20crucial%20for%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20and%20enable%20agriculture%20in%20an%20otherwise%20arid%20environment.%20For%20human%20use%2C%20they%20feed%20springs%20used%20for%20drinking%20water%2C%20supply%20water%20for%20wells%2C%20and%20support%20traditional%20water%20management%20systems%20like%20%3Cem%3Ezings%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ponds)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eyura%3C%2Fem%3E%20(channels)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20stored%20water%20in%20aquifers%20helps%20Leh%20withstand%20periods%20of%20low%20precipitation%2C%20providing%20resilience%20against%20drought.%20This%20consistent%20water%20supply%20allows%20for%20urban%20development%20and%20supports%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F282723%2Fbest-homestays-in-ladakh-things-to-do-in-leh-local-experience%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20tourism%20%3C%2Fa%3Eindustry%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20and%20properly%20managing%20this%20invisible%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20crucial%20for%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20sustainable%20future%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20face%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20increasing%20water%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20crucial%20lifeline%20is%20under%20severe%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Slowly%20poisoning%20the%20very%20veins%20that%20sustain%20us%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rising%20tourist%20footfall%2C%20unplanned%20development%20and%20poor%20water%20management%20practices%2C%20Dr%20Chorol%E2%80%99s%20nearly%20seven-year%20research%20into%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20come%20up%20with%20some%20troubling%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecline%20in%20water%20quality%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9COver%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20observed%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20water%20quality.%20For%20instance%2C%20Total%20Dissolved%20Solids%20(TDS)%20levels%20have%20increased%20by%20about%2030%25%20in%20some%20areas%2C%20from%20an%20average%20of%20300%20mg%2FL%20to%20over%20400%20mg%2FL.%20This%20rapid%20increase%20is%20alarming.%20To%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20serious%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20let%20me%20share%20some%20of%20our%20key%20findings%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20drinking%20water%2C%20we%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20our%20samples%20were%20of%20extremely%20poor%20quality%2C%20and%20another%203.57%25%20were%20poor.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20that%2092.86%25%20were%20only%20of%20average%20quality%2C%20and%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20samples%20in%20the%20good%20or%20excellent%20categories%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNitrate%20levels%20have%20risen%20by%20up%20to%2050%25%20in%20certain%20wells%2C%20approaching%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20limit%20of%2050%20mg%2FL%20in%20some%20cases.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20also%20detected%20increasing%20concentrations%20of%20heavy%20metals%20like%20chromium%20and%20cadmium%20with%20some%20samples%20showing%20levels%20two%20to%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20what%20we%20observed%20six%20years%20ago.%20For%20irrigation%20water%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20equally%20worrying.%20We%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20samples%20were%20very%20poor%2C%2042.86%25%20were%20poor%2C%20and%2053.57%25%20were%20average.%20This%20indicates%20a%20widespread%20issue%20with%20water%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20in%20groundwater%20chemistry%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20chemical%20composition%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20altered%20noticeably.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20increased%20levels%20of%20ions%20like%20chloride%2C%20sulphate%2C%20and%20sodium%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20associated%20with%20human%20activities.%20For%20example%2C%20chloride%20concentrations%20have%20risen%20by%20about%2040%25%20in%20some%20wells%20over%20the%20six%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20change%20suggests%20contamination%20from%20sources%20like%20improper%20sewage%20disposal%20and%20the%20concentration%20of%20major%20cations%20has%20increased%2C%20following%20the%20order%20of%20calcium%2C%20magnesium%2C%20sodium%2C%20and%20potassium.%20We%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20higher%20levels%20of%20sodium%2C%20potassium%2C%20fluoride%2C%20and%20nitrates%2C%20which%20we%20believe%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20increased%20use%20of%20agrochemicals%20in%20agriculture%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20the%20elevated%20levels%20of%20heavy%20metals%20we%E2%80%99re%20detecting.%20Iron%2C%20manganese%2C%20chromium%2C%20nickel%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20copper%20are%20all%20present%20at%20levels%20exceeding%20permissible%20limits%20in%20many%20of%20the%20samples%20studied%20by%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20contamination%20from%20various%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20sewage%20leaking%20from%20poorly%20maintained%20septic%20systems%2C%20agricultural%20runoff%20from%20fertilisers%2C%20waste%20from%20increased%20tourism%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20proper%20wastewater%20treatment%20facilities.%20Each%20of%20these%20sources%20might%20seem%20small%20on%20its%20own%20but%20together%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20having%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20our%20water%20quality.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20complex%20issue%2C%20but%20understanding%20it%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20addressing%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh%20groundwater%20is%20suffering%20due%20to%20poor%20sewage%20management%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365888%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20sewer%20cleaning%20truck%20in%20Leh%3A%20Sewage%20management%20is%20a%20serious%20problem%20in%20this%20high-altitude%20town%20(Image%20courtesy%20Shutterstock%2F%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shutterstock.com%2Fg%2FOliverFoerstner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOliver%20Foerstner%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealth%20risks%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20we%20found%20that%20certain%20heavy%20metals%2C%20such%20as%20chromium%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20nickel%2C%20present%20in%20the%20groundwater%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20increase%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349895%2Fhow-to-deal-with-cancer-diagnosis-regular-health-checkup-turbt-battle-india-chemo-therapy-ninad-raikar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk%20of%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20risk%20is%20particularly%20concerning%20for%20children%2C%20who%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20effects%20of%20these%20contaminants%20due%20to%20their%20developing%20bodies%20and%20higher%20water%20intake%20relative%20to%20their%20body%20weight.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20carcinogenic%20risk%2C%20we%20also%20identified%20non-carcinogenic%20health%20risks%20posed%20by%20chromium%20in%20the%20groundwater%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20heavy%20metals%2C%20her%20study%20also%20investigated%20the%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20exposure%20in%20the%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hazard%20quotient%20analysis%20revealed%20that%20the%20oral%20pathway%2C%20i.e.%20drinking%20contaminated%20water%2C%20was%20the%20primary%20route%20of%20exposure%20for%20all%20age%20groups.%20Fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20were%20found%20to%20be%20the%20major%20contributors%20to%20these%20health%20risks%20with%20children%20and%20infants%20being%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20their%20effects.%20Fluoride%2C%20when%20consumed%20in%20excess%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20dental%20and%20skeletal%20fluorosis%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20discolouration%20and%20damage%20to%20the%20teeth%20and%20bones.%20Nitrate%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20interfere%20with%20the%20blood%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20carry%20oxygen%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20condition%20called%20methemoglobinemia%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20dangerous%20for%20infants%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EImpact%20of%20climate%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%2027%20July%20to%2030%20July%202024%2C%20around%2012%20flights%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20touch%20down%20at%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F139355%2Fbakula-rinpoche-ladakhi-monastery-democracy-mongolia-sushma-swaraj%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKushok%20Bakula%20Rinpoche%3C%2Fa%3E%20Airport%20while%20many%20more%20were%20cancelled.%20The%20maximum%20operating%20temperature%20of%20Leh%20airport%20is%2032%C2%B0C%20but%20on%2028%20July%2C%20the%20Leh%20division%20recorded%2033.5%C2%B0C%20as%20per%20the%20Metrology%20Centre%20of%20Ladakh.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20temperature%20recorded%20in%20the%20Kargil%20division%20was%2037.5%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELadakh%20was%20burning%20this%20summer%20because%20of%20a%20huge%20deficit%20in%20rainfall.%20It%20received%203%20mm%20of%20rainfall%20till%20the%20start%20of%20August%20as%20against%20the%20normal%20of%2015%20mm.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lack%20of%20precipitation%20and%20intense%20heat%20wave%20has%20dried%20out%20the%20soil%2C%20causing%20crops%20to%20wither%20and%20trees%20to%20require%20more%20water.%20Meanwhile%2C%20groundwater%20exploitation%20by%20drilling%20more%20borewells%20has%20further%20accelerated%20the%20decline%20in%20groundwater%20levels%20and%20reserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20all%20know%2C%20Leh%20is%20located%20in%20a%20high-altitude%20desert%20region%2C%20where%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20water%20for%20our%20aquifers%20is%20the%20melting%20of%20glaciers%20and%20snowpack%20in%20the%20surrounding%20mountains.%20However%2C%20as%20recent%20events%20indicate%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20causing%20significant%20alterations%20to%20this%20delicate%20balance%2C%20leading%20to%20severe%20consequences%20for%20our%20groundwater%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Overview%20of%20Leh%20Town%3A%20Climate%20change%20is%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20region's%20groundwater%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Town-1726234110-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365898%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOverview%20of%20Leh%20Town%3A%20Climate%20change%20is%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20(Image%20courtesy%20Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%20is%20the%20increase%20in%20global%20temperatures.%20The%20rapid%20melting%20of%20glaciers%20leads%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20water%20flow%20during%20the%20summer%20months%2C%20but%20it%20also%20means%20that%20there%20is%20less%20water%20stored%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ice%20to%20sustain%20the%20flow%20during%20dry%20seasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20also%20altering%20precipitation%20patterns%20in%20Leh.%20We%20are%20experiencing%20more%20frequent%20and%20intense%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20such%20as%20heavy%20rainfall%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F323311%2Fhimachal-pradesh-floods-landslides-north-india-heavy-rains-kullu-kangra-mandi-emergency-helpline%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflash%20floods%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20these%20events%20do%20contribute%20to%20the%20recharge%20of%20our%20aquifers%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20they%20also%20lead%20to%20increased%20surface%20runoff%20and%20soil%20erosion.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20rainwater%20is%20lost%20before%20it%20can%20percolate%20into%20the%20ground%20and%20replenish%20our%20aquifers%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnother%20factor%20to%20consider%20is%20the%20changing%20vegetation%20cover%20in%20the%20region.%20As%20temperatures%20rise%20and%20precipitation%20patterns%20change%2C%20we%20are%20observing%20shifts%20in%20the%20local%20ecosystem.%20Some%20native%20plant%20species%20like%20seabuckthorn%2C%20willow%20and%20poplar%20that%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20retaining%20moisture%20and%20promoting%20groundwater%20recharge%20are%20struggling%20to%20adapt%20to%20these%20new%20conditions.%20The%20loss%20of%20these%20species%20can%20further%20exacerbate%20the%20problem%20of%20reduced%20aquifer%20recharge%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBroken%20sewage%20system%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20state%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20sewage%20system%20is%20a%20significant%20concern%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20groundwater.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20town%20lacks%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20efficient%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F302015%2Fboson-whitewater-bengaluru-startup-converts-stp-water-to-high-quality-potable-drinking-water%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esewage%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E%20system%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20the%20deterioration%20of%20our%20groundwater%20resources%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20present%2C%20most%20of%20the%20households%20and%20establishments%20in%20Leh%20rely%20on%20individual%20septic%20tanks%20or%20dry%20soak%20pits%20for%20wastewater%20disposal.%20While%20these%20systems%20are%20designed%20to%20treat%20wastewater%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20they%20are%20often%20poorly%20maintained%2C%20overloaded%2C%20or%20improperly%20constructed.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20untreated%20or%20partially%20treated%20sewage%20can%20seep%20into%20the%20ground%2C%20contaminating%20our%20aquifers%20with%20harmful%20pollutants%20such%20as%20nitrates%2C%20bacteria%2C%20and%20viruses%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20rapid%20growth%20of%20tourism%20and%20urbanisation%20in%20Leh%20has%20put%20additional%20strain%20on%20the%20existing%20sewage%20infrastructure.%20The%20increased%20volume%20of%20wastewater%20generated%20by%20hotels%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20other%20commercial%20establishments%20often%20exceeds%20the%20capacity%20of%20their%20septic%20systems%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20overflow%20of%20untreated%20sewage%20into%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22We%20are%20dealing%20with%20a%20broken%20sewage%20system%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-4-1-1726234320-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365904%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20sewage%20system%20is%20a%20significant%20problem%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20groundwater%20(Image%20courtesy%20Shutterstock%2F%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shutterstock.com%2Fg%2FOliverFoerstner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOliver%20Foerstner%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20study%20has%20revealed%20elevated%20levels%20of%20nitrates%2C%20faecal%20coliform%20bacteria%2C%20and%20other%20contaminants%20in%20many%20groundwater%20samples%2C%20indicating%20the%20impact%20of%20sewage%20infiltration.%20These%20contaminants%20pose%20serious%20health%20risks%2C%20especially%20to%20children%20and%20the%20elderly%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20local%20administration%20has%20taken%20some%20steps%20to%20address%20the%20issue%2C%20such%20as%20promoting%20the%20construction%20of%20improved%20septic%20tanks%20and%20encouraging%20the%20use%20of%20eco-friendly%20toilets%2C%20these%20measures%20have%20been%20insufficient%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20the%20growing%20challenges%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20increased%20demand%20for%20water%20due%20to%20population%20growth%20and%20tourism%20puts%20additional%20pressure%20on%20our%20groundwater%20resources.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20more%20water%20is%20extracted%20from%20the%20aquifers%2C%20the%20natural%20recharge%20process%20is%20unable%20to%20keep%20pace%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20groundwater%20levels%20and%20potential%20depletion%20of%20our%20aquifers%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGroundwater%20extraction%20in%20Leh%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiwaponline.com%2Fjwcc%2Farticle%2F15%2F4%2F1459%2F100946%2FGroundwater-scenario-under-climate-change-and%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20April%202024%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Water%20and%20Climate%20Change%20led%20by%20Dr%20Farooq%20Ahmad%20Dar%20%E2%80%94%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Geography%20and%20Disaster%20Management%2C%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%94%20groundwater%20extraction%20and%20decline%20in%20Leh%20has%20increased%20significantly%20in%20recent%20years.%20Here%20are%20two%20key%20data%20points%20from%20the%20study%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Well%20drilling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%201997%2C%20there%20were%20only%2010%20drilled%20wells%20in%20Leh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBy%202020%2C%20the%20total%20number%20of%20wells%20had%20grown%20to%202%2C659.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20represents%20an%20increase%20of%20about%20115%20new%20wells%20per%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Groundwater%20extraction%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGroundwater%20extraction%20increased%20by%20approximately%2026%25%20from%202009%20to%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAbout%20seven%20million%20cubic%20metres%20of%20water%20are%20drawn%20annually%20from%20wells.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Dr%20Dar%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20figures%20should%20raise%20alarm%20bells%20in%20the%20region.%20In%20simple%20language%2C%20these%20figures%20highlight%20the%20current%20scenario%20of%20groundwater%20pumping.%20When%20more%20people%20will%20shift%20to%20groundwater%20and%20drill%20their%20own%20wells%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20check%20on%20the%20reserves.%20Groundwater%20is%20a%20State%20Subject%20and%20that%20means%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20local%20administration%20to%20have%20legal%20checks%20on%20its%20use%20and%20misuse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20scenario%2C%20when%20more%20wells%20will%20be%20drilled%2C%20which%20we%20estimated%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20115%20wells%20per%20year%20(these%20figures%20are%20based%20on%20limited%20data%2C%20the%20rate%20could%20be%20even%20higher)%2C%20the%20reserves%20will%20be%2